{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AsTPYj8HcHkZX89YPrRrCT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see `RAY_RAYLET_PID: \"1\"` hardcoded. In Ray 2.x, this environment variable is normally set to the actual raylet process PID at runtime. Hardcoding it to \"1\" could cause a conflict, especially when multiple pods use the same PID.\n\nBut looking at this again - if this worked for 2 workers, why doesn't it work for 4? Unless the issue is that GCS has a node limit or something.\n\nWait, let me re-check. The new pods have 2 restarts and are currently Running (READY 1/1). But the Ray status still shows 3 nodes. \n\nLooking at the GCS `RegisterNode` stats more carefully - there were 6 total registrations. The head registered once, the first two workers registered successfully, but the new workers are registering and then dying shortly after, which suggests they're hitting some resource constraint or hitting the hardcoded PID conflict when multiple raylets try to use PID \"1\".\n\nThe real issue is that on their second restart attempt, these new workers can't even establish a gRPC connection to GCS - they're failing before registration. This is strange because we confirmed port 6379 is reachable, and their first restart attempt succeeded in connecting. I'm wondering if there's a GCS state issue where it's rejecting the connection because it still sees the node as registered and dead, or if something else is blocking the gRPC handshake on the second attempt.\n\nWhen I tried to exec into one of the new worker pods earlier, I got a \"cannot exec in a deleted state\" error, which suggests these pods are cycling through rapid delete/create cycles. Let me check whether the new worker pods are actually stable right now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2226,"cache_read_input_tokens":48954,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2226},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34abd7e5-b560-4ada-abf9-16e9c2b88f15","uuid":"1d1f371a-acc1-4906-88b6-1b03f1b2de85","request_id":"req_011Cc6eXU2KyeDregwuRWACa"}
