ring with GCS and retrying, which suggests the bootstrap protocol might be handling retries differently than what the new workers are experiencing.\n\nLet me trace through the network setup: the head pod is at 10.244.0.182 with ports 6379, 10001, and 8265 all open, and the new workers at 10.244.0.185 and 10.244.0.186 are on the same node. So network connectivity shouldn't be the issue. I need to check whether the GCS service is actually accepting connections from the new worker pods.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2002,"cache_read_input_tokens":68088,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2002},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34abd7e5-b560-4ada-abf9-16e9c2b88f15","uuid":"bbaadd68-7b10-4ca6-9d29-9924182d5120","request_id":"req_011Cc6etQmhY7B8cCaLTmWJx"}
